# Laravel Development Rules

## General
- Follow Laravel 12 conventions
- Use PHP 8.5 features when appropriate
- Prefer Eloquent ORM over raw SQL
- Use route model binding when possible

## Controllers
- Controllers should be thin
- Business logic should be moved to services when it grows
- Validate requests using FormRequest classes

## Models
- Use Eloquent relationships
- Use fillable or guarded properties
- Avoid putting heavy logic in models

## Database
- Use migrations for schema changes
- Use foreign keys and indexes where needed
- Prefer soft deletes for user-generated content

## Views
- Use Blade templating
- Keep views simple
- Move reusable components to Blade components

## Security
- Always use CSRF protection
- Validate all incoming requests
- Use Laravel authentication middleware

## Chat App Specific
- Messages belong to users
- Messages should support text and file attachments
- Chat should load the latest 50 messages initially
